messages.text:
How can I force JSON.jl to serialize nans not as null, but "nan"?
```julia&gt; JSON.json([0.1, NaN, 0, 2.2])
"[0.1,null,0.0,2.2]"```
But I need this:
```"[0.1,"nan",0.0,2.2]"```
Because this how it works on JS side:
```var json = "[0.1, \"nan\", 0, 2.2]";
var myTypedArray = new Float32Array(JSON.parse(json));
console.log(myTypedArray);

&gt; Float32Array [0.10000000149011612, NaN, 0, 2.200000047683716]```

